Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 -           ]
Title: WIPER / WASHER: WASHER MOTOR: REMOVAL; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

REMOVAL

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE FRONT WHEEL RH

Click here

2. REMOVE FRONT FENDER LINER RH

(a) Remove the 3 screws.

(b) Remove the 5 screws and grommet.

(c) Using a screwdriver, turn each pin 90 degrees and remove the 2 pin hold clips.

*a

90°

(d) for Rough Road Area Specification Vehicles:

(1) Remove the clip.

(e) Remove the 9 clips and front fender liner RH.

3. DRAIN WASHER FLUID

(a) w/o Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the washer hose from the windshield washer motor and pump assembly, and drain the washer fluid.

HINT:

Use a container to collect the washer fluid.

(b) w/ Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the rear washer hose from the windshield washer motor and pump assembly, and drain the washer fluid.

HINT:

Use a container to collect the washer fluid.

4. REMOVE WINDSHIELD WASHER MOTOR AND PUMP ASSEMBLY

(a) w/o Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the connector.

Remove in this Direction

(2) Remove the windshield washer motor and pump assembly as shown in the illustration.

(b) w/ Rear Wiper:

(1) Disconnect the washer hose.

Remove in this Direction

(2) Disconnect the connector.

(3) Remove the windshield washer motor and pump assembly as shown in the illustration.
